layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Estate & Legacy Planning | Wealth Transfer Strategies | Capital Wealth"
description: "Protect and transfer your wealth to future generations efficiently. Estate planning coordination, trust strategies, and tax-efficient legacy planning in Lehi, Utah."
breadcrumbs:
  - { name: "Home", url: "/" }
  - { name: "Services", url: "/services/" }
  - { name: "Estate & Legacy Planning", url: "/services/estate-planning/" }
faqSchema:
  - question: "Do you draft wills and trusts?"
    answer: "No, we don't practice law. We coordinate with estate planning attorneys to ensure your legal documents align with your financial strategy. We'll refer you to a qualified attorney and work with them to implement the plan."
  - question: "Should I convert my IRA to a Roth for my heirs?"
    answer: "Often, yes. Inherited traditional IRAs are now subject to the 10-year rule, which can push heirs into high tax brackets. Converting to a Roth during your lifetime (when you control the timing and tax impact) can save your heirs tens of thousands in taxes. We model this scenario as part of your estate plan."
  - question: "What's a Qualified Charitable Distribution (QCD)?"
    answer: "A QCD allows you to donate up to $105,000 per year directly from your IRA to charity (after age 70½). The distribution counts toward your RMD but doesn't increase your taxable income — a powerful strategy for reducing taxes and supporting causes you care about."
  - question: "When should I update my estate plan?"
    answer: "Review your estate plan annually and update it after major life events like marriage, divorce, births, deaths, significant asset changes, or moves to a different state. We conduct an annual beneficiary audit for all clients to ensure your designations still match your intentions."
  - question: "What happens to my beneficiaries if I don't have an estate plan?"
    answer: "Without an estate plan, state law decides who gets your assets, courts appoint guardians for minor children, and your family may face lengthy probate processes and unnecessary taxes. Proper planning ensures your wishes are honored and your loved ones are protected."
---

